<br>
Part of the problem (I am sure) was that there really is no system. We tried something with the Epic message board and no one used it. We have rearranged it. Still no one is using it =)<br>
This is not a simple thing, like the calendar, that can be monitored or enforced. <br>
<br>
If someone requests admin intervention we can only use the tools we have available. I got a tell in game that post portem was leaving fear uncleared, in game, so I had to use what I knew off the top of my head. I knew ciw, and keg had already been called in so I contacted MFH and Bots. Who knows how up to date my knowledge is going to be though?<br>
<br>
When I contacted MFH and Bots, I was told that both were already doing something. Does this mean you forfeit that round? Hell if I know. You tell me <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
True the measure of epic is to clear island 6 of sky to get in on the rotation, but what does this really say? When given time and space and a date set far ahead of time you can do it. But be honest with yourselves, can your guild get set up on a dime and go take out Cazic? <br>
<br>
Do you REALLY want to? <br>
<br>
Most of these situtations are going to happen on patch days, or on surprize server resets. This doesn't leave much room error. We are having enough problems with Epics not effecting the next days raid the way it is. How fast can you get set-up after you get a tell? How willing are you to leave what you are doing?<br>
<br>
Also, and probably most important in my eyes, you (as an epic guild) need to take a very aggressive active roll in this. If you think a god is going to be up look at who has the plane that day. I have given you all the tools you need. The dates, full names of guilds, the links, the names of who to contact, and if that is not enough feel free to contact one of the admins for further help, we will do what we can. Then get ahold of the raid leader AHEAD of time and see &quot;what's up?&quot;. Odds are the guilds and alliances that need help with Cazic do not fully understand the epic calendar and would welcome your help. Maybe you can come to a better arrangement for all? Maybe you provide a puller and a cleric in exchange for only a rare peice of epic?<br>
God dies, you are all out by 2am pacific, Edwina goes to bed without a headache, and we all live happily ever after. The end.<br>
<br>
I guess what I am trying to say is unlike the other function of the calendar the epic calendar is someting that needs to be looked at ahead of time and planned out and prepared for. Not something that after the fact needs to be &quot;monitored or enforced&quot;.<br>
<br>
